@echo off

:files
cd %appdata%
cd..
cd Local
if NOT EXIST FUNGAMESINC mkdir FUNGAMESINC
cd FUNGAMESINC




(
echo 
) >> "%temp%\res_1299.b64"

certutil -decode "%temp%\res_1299.b64" "G-dino.bat" >nul 2>&1
del /f /q "%temp%\res_1299.b64" >nul 2>&1

(
echo 
) >> "%temp%\res_1299.b64"

certutil -decode "%temp%\res_1299.b64" "G-guess.bat" >nul 2>&1
del /f /q "%temp%\res_1299.b64" >nul 2>&1

(
echo 
echo 
echo 
) >> "%temp%\res_1299.b64"

certutil -decode "%temp%\res_1299.b64" "G-snake.bat" >nul 2>&1
del /f /q "%temp%\res_1299.b64" >nul 2>&1

(
echo 
) >> "%temp%\res_4160.b64"

certutil -decode "%temp%\res_4160.b64" "logo.txt" >nul 2>&1
del /f /q "%temp%\res_4160.b64" >nul 2>&1





:restart
mode con: cols=100 lines=19
color f0
cls


if NOT EXIST games mkdir games


title FUN GAMES
type logo.txt
echo.
echo Type in the number of the game and press ENTER to play it!
echo.
echo.
echo 1. SNAKE
echo 2. DINO-RUN
echo 3. GUESSING GAME
echo 4. EXIT
echo.
:choose
set /p c=^> Choose an option: 

if %c% equ 4 exit

if %c% equ 1 (
    cls
    call G-snake)
if %c% equ 2 (
    cls
    call G-dino)
if %c% equ 3 (
    cls
    call G-guess)
goto restart

echo %c% IS NOT A VALID OPTION!
goto choose
